  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The proposed development, by reason of its bulk, massing, scale, detailed design, position and location would result in an obtrusive and incompatible form of development which adversely disrupts the established grain of the area and would consequently fail to preserve or enhance the area within which the property is located. As such the proposed development is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising Site Capacity Through the Design-Led Approach) and D4 (Delivering Good Design) of the London Plan 2021, policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) of the Local Plan 2033 and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD 2009.<br></p>",
    "<p>The proposal, by reason of its failure to provide a contribution for affordable housing, represents an unsustainable form of development. As such the proposal is contrary to policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP13 (Affordable Housing) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020), policy H4 (Delivering Affordable Housing) of the London Plan and the S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).<br></p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;Insufficient information has been submitted in regard to the impact of trees as a result of this application. The Local Planning Authority is therefore unable to fully assess the merits or otherwise of this proposal and its impact on the surrounding trees of amenity value, contrary to policy G7 (Trees and Woodlands) of the London Plan and policy LP51 (Tree Management and Landscaping) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "<p>Insufficient information has been submitted in regard to the cycle storage arrangements to alleviate the Council's concern the development would have insufficient and inadequate cycle parking provision, resulting in adverse impacts to road networks, contrary to Local Plan 2033 policy (LP42 Walking and Cycling) and London Plan policy T5 (Cycling).&nbsp;</p>",
    "<p>Insufficient information has been submitted in regard to the refuse and recycling arrangements to alleviate the Council's concern the development would have insufficient and inadequate waste and refuse provision, resulting in adverse litter, odour and pollution impacts, contrary to Local Plan 2033 policies LP57 (Waste) and LP58 (Improving the Environment - Pollution).&nbsp;</p>",
    "<p>The proposed development, by reason of poor natural light provision to the basement unit, along with the provision of inadequate outdoor amenity space to the proposed residential accommodation, would result in the provision of an unacceptable standard of residential accommodation, to the detriment of the living conditions of future occupiers. As such the proposed development is contrary to policy D6 (Housing Quality and Standards) and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Local Plan 2033 and the guidance contained within the Mayor of London's Housing SPG.</p><div><br></div>"
  ],
